"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses `np.insert` to modify the shape of the sub-arrays in `arr`. `np.insert` returns a new array with the inserted values, but it does not modify the original array in place. This will lead to a shape mismatch error because `arr` has a fixed shape of (3, 4), and inserting an element will change the shape of the sub-arrays to (5,).\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5,6\\n<    arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)\\n---\\n>    arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)[:4]\\n\"\n}"